BEGIN_PGML

It is the final seconds of an ice hockey game between the Flyers and the Bruins. The Bruins are down by [`1`] point. With [`20`] [`s`] left in the game, the Bruins pull the goalie and have him play as a forward in an attempt to tie the game. The Flyers successfully defend their goal for [`9`] [`s`]. With only [`[$t]`] [`s`] remaining on the game clock, a Flyer shoots the puck on the ice past the skates and sticks of the other players and toward the Bruins' goal. The puck is [`[$s]`] [`m`] from the goal when it leaves the stick with an initial horizontal velocity of [`[$v]`] [`m/s`]. The shot is perfectly directed toward the empty goal, but the ice slows the puck down at a constant rate of [`[$a]`] [`m/s^2`] as it slides toward the goal. None of the Bruins can stop the puck before it reaches the goal.

*a)* How far from the goal is the puck when the game clock reaches zero and the horn sounds to end the game? (_Answer with a positive number if the puck has not entered the goal yet and answer with a negative number otherwise._)

[`d=`] [_____] [`m`]  

*b)* Do the Flyers win the game by [`1`] or [`2`] points?

[@ $mcCorrect->menu() @]*

END_PGML

ANS($d->cmp);
ANS($mcCorrect->cmp);

